The text on the FBGA package of the '''Micron''' RAM reads "K9N5 OUG12 D9MNL" (FBGA Code: D9MNL).
I am assuming this device uses a D8:C7:C8 OUI (it's on various MAC labels affixed to the FCC EUT and its wireless modules).
This device is identical to the [[Aruba Networks AP-134]] with the exception of the antennas. This device uses internal antennas the AP-134 uses external antennas.
